				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I meant to add:
<br />

<br />
I think this type of idea could please any mage.
<br />

<br />
The earth pet gives us a pet that is viable for tanking, but not very good DPS.  This could be used in groups with no melees as well as for the solo mage who needs a pet durable enough to survive while the mage nukes a mob down.
<br />

<br />
The fire pet would provide us the DPS increase we need in groups, while eliminating the need to position the pet behind the mob.  Pet positioning is a needless pain.  Of course, ripostes would need to be delt with somehow I suppose.
<br />

<br />
The air pet would please those who are happy with the pets we have now.  His stun is also a very useful addition to groups because he reduces dmg delt and stops casters and runners.  Perhaps his presence could also add a slight amount of mana regen to the entire group?
<br />

<br />
The water pet would provide us with a utility that no other class currently provides.  He could heal other pets near him while still dealing acceptable DPS and leaving the mage free to deal burst dps.  This would be a great raid enhancement because it would allow pets to be used on mobs with nasty AEs.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
